JEDDAH: The Organization of Islamic Cooperation has welcomed a $1 million donation from Nigeria for Afghanistan. OIC Secretary-General Hissein Brahim Taha said the donation came in time to add new momentum to the organization’s efforts to help ease the humanitarian situation in Afghanistan and to meet the needs of millions of Afghans. The OIC has appealed to all member states, stakeholders and partners to come on board and make contributions to the humanitarian trust fund for Afghanistan through the bank account reserved for this fund at the Islamic Development Bank.